HEADWORD: Blue-bonnet
<hw>Blue"-bon`net</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A broad, flat Scottish
cap of blue woolen, or one wearing such cap; a Scotchman.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant. Same as
<er>Bluebottle</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The European blue titmouse
(<spn>Parus c⟦oe⟧ruleus</spn>); the bluecap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Blue book</ent>⟦br⟧
